                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Truce Supervision Headquarters, at Haifa, addressed identical notes on behalf
                    of the Acting Mediator to the Government of Egypt and to the provisional
                    Government of Israel, which called for withdrawal of the armed forces of both
                    sides from positions in the Negeb they had occupied at the outbreak of
                    hostilities on October 14; for text, see <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi
                        rend="italic">3rd yr., Supplement for October 1948</hi>, page 70. This
                    source dates the notes October 26; yet Mr. Bunche in referring to them before
                    the Security Council, dates them October 25 (<gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>,
                        <hi rend="italic">3rd yr., No. 121</hi>, page 23, and <hi rend="italic">No.
                        122</hi>, page 3).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
